NAME
       diskinfo - report attached disks, partitions and mounts

SYNOPSIS
       diskinfo

DESCRIPTION
       Enumerates every block device returned by cervus_disk_info(2),
       prints its model, transport, capacity, MBR partition table, list
       of mount points, and statvfs-derived usage for each mounted
       partition.

       Transport is inferred from the kernel-assigned device name:
       'hd*' devices are reported as ATA/IDE (PIO); 'sd*' as
       AHCI/SATA (DMA); 'nvme*' as NVMe.

SEE ALSO
       mount(1), lsblk(1), mkfs(1)
